value.value: A fractured quality where the fracture traverses the bone perpendicular to the axis of the bone.
A fractured quality in which one of the fragments is driven into another fragment.
A fractured quality where the fracture runs parallel to the long axis of a bone.
A fractured quality where the fracture occurs at a plane oblique to the long axis of the bone.
A fractured quality that occurs when torque (a rotating force) is applied along the axis of a bone.
A fractured quality that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.
A fractured quality in which the fragment of bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.
A decreased quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decreased magnitude in proportion to the magnitude of another entity.

definition.value: Example: decreased proportion of CD4 T cells relative to total T cells.

value.value: An increased quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's increased magnitude in proportion to the magnitude of another entity.

definition.value: Example: increased proportion of CD4 T cells relative to total T cells.

value.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's components being torn, typically used for soft tissues or membranes.
The rate or speed of the change in in number of a population.
The rate or speed of the change in size of an individual entity.
Existing or functioning as though broken into separate parts; disorganized; disunified.

definition.value: Moved to a child of wholeness because broken implies a trauma and fragmented could be caused by a developmental process. See HP:0100168 Fragmented epiphyses as an example.

value.value: Red due to increase blood circulation in a defined area.

definition.value: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise male of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.
The term intersex is popular in use, but may be considered offensive when applied to humans. DSD can be expanded multiple ways to 'disorders/differences of sexual development/differentiation'.

value.value: A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have two stamens.
A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have only one stamen.
A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to male at a later life stage.
A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to female at a later life stage.
A protogynous quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.
A protandrous quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

definition.value: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise female of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.
The term intersex is popular in use, but may be considered offensive when applied to humans. DSD can be expanded multiple ways to 'disorders/differences of sexual development/differentiation'.

value.value: A quality inhering in a process by virtue of that process having a population or part of a population, where population is defined as a collection of individuals from the same taxonomic class distinguished by one or more characteristics, as participants.
A quality denoting the lack of a physical entity or object, such as a chemical.

definition.value: A quality denoting the lack of a process or function.

value.value: A quality denoting the lack of an anatomical entity or cellular component.

definition.value: Absence of anatomical entity should only be used when all of the entity is absent. For example, absent teeth would mean all teeth are absent not some teeth are absent.

value.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to deform by heating.
A quality inhering in a cell by virtue of the ratio between the volume of its nucleus and the volume of its cytoplasm.
A quality inhering in a cell by virtue of the cell having a high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio.

definition.value: A high nuclear/cytolasmic ratio is 70% or higher.
A rate which is relatively normal.
A quality of an object that has a value that is normal or average.
An acidity which is relatively normal.
A adhesivity which is relatively normal or average.
An affinity which is relatively normal or average.
An age which is relatively normal or average.
An avidity which is relatively normal or average.
A behavioural quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting normal or average activity.
A cellular motility which is normal or average.
A coiling which is normal or average.
A concentration which is relatively normal or average.
A contractility which is relatively normal or average.
A coordination which is relatively normal or average.
A curvature which is relatively normal or average.
A distance which is relatively normal or average.
An efficiency which is relatively normal or average.
An elasticity which is relatively normal or average.
A fecundity which is relatively normal or average.
A female fertility which is relatively normal or average.
A female receptivity which is relatively normal or average.
A fertility which is relatively normal or average.
